paragraph.def:
the terms “a Contracting Party” and “the other Contracting Party” mean the
                        Government of the Federal Republic of Germany or the Government of the Hong
                        Kong Special Administrative Region, as the context requires;

subparagraph.content:
in the case of the Federal Republic of Germany, the Federal
                            Ministry of Finance or the agency to which it has delegated its
                            powers;

paragraph.def:
the term “company” means any
                        body corporate or any entity which is treated as a body corporate for tax
                        purposes;

paragraph.continued:
Where by reason of this sub-paragraph an enterprise is an enterprise
                       of both Contracting Parties, the competent authorities of the Contracting
                       Parties shall determine its status by mutual agreement;

subparagraph.content:
in the case of taxes withheld at source, in respect of amounts paid
                            on or after the first day of January of the calendar year next following
                            that in which notice is given;

in the case of other taxes, in respect of taxes levied for periods
                            beginning on or after the first day of January of the calendar year next
                            following that in which notice is given;
